[step 2] fusion A/B
  - 3 runs against step 1 baseline: no_fusion, no_multi_add, no_graph_opt
  - findings:
    * DISABLE_FUSION: +2.76% total / -2.80% predict — lower bound; only
      scheduler-level pattern fusion (RMS_NORM_MUL, ADD chains) is affected,
      graph-builder Phase 3 fusions are permanently on
    * DISABLE_MULTI_ADD: +0.01% — multi-add pattern isn't firing for Qwen3.5-9B
    * DISABLE_GRAPH_OPTIMIZE: +3.68% total / -1.64% predict
      - ARGMAX alone: 5.9ms → 1507.6ms (255× slowdown on full-vocab argmax)
      - graph-optimize is folding MUL_MAT_VEC q5_K 248320x4096 + ARGMAX into
        a single dispatch; losing this costs 1.5s of GPU time per 3 runs
      - also: MTP acceptance rose from 69.9% to 73.5% when graph-optimize was
        disabled — numerical precision shift in the order-of-ops
  - combined lower bound: ~6.4% of total GPU time is paid for by fusion + graph
    optimize knobs (graph-builder fused ops from Phase 3 would be at least as
    valuable again, not measured here)
