  - BIG FINDING: prompt-eval batched MUL_MAT q4_K 12288x218 runs at
    6342 GFLOPS on Vega vs 23312 GFLOPS on Navi (3.68x) — that's
    the prompt-eval speedup in one number
  - vocab head q5_k 248320x4096 (the 256-VGPR Vega limit) gets 1.72x
    GFLOPS on Navi thanks to wave32 RDNA2 occupancy model
  - RMS_NORM_MUL 1.69x on Navi (L2 cache improvement)
  - IMPLICATION: Navi 21 already on-board, 2x VRAM (16 GiB vs 8), and
    1.56x generation throughput with zero code changes. User should
    strongly consider making Navi 21 the primary inference target.
